<br>
The most important thing is just to take your time.  If you use mend wait for it to pop... same thing with stone stance.  Stay patient and you should do fine.<br>
<br>
1) things to take...  some kind of gate.  I was a moron and did not do this because when you look at the map a number of portals are marked.  They just take you back to the zone in location.<br>
<br>
2) Invis pots.  I went in invis and did fd on entry.  It was my first time in zone and so I had a good look around and figured out my orientation.<br>
<br>
Then I run and jumped off the zone in area to the north west and FD on the way down.  After that I did a quick move FD when the over in front of the west corridor in the basement to have a look around.<br>
<br>
3)  ITU pots.  I had an invis to undead 10 pot and found it to be a big help.  Once in the coridor and after making the turn to the north all but one of the mobs was undead.  I did a /q to clear agro and when I got back in used ITU to make it all the way to the end for the quest turn in.<br>
<br>
After that I would just FD to a clear area of the coridor and do a /q to clear agro again and then gate out.   Instead I ran to the center of the basement to the marked portal only to find myself back up top at the initial zone in spot to HS.  It took some chating with others in zone to get a port out when a group was done hunting in one of the wings and all was done.<br>
<br>
<br>
I did find ITU pots to be very usefull, but did get agro from one mob while doing the turn in.  It took a while thow and I could converse with the NPC with ITU up and the undead in the room left me alone untill a romer came into the room and agroed.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps and it was a lot of fun.<br>
<br>
